Your middle-thirties were not very good
for you, were they?

1364
01:34:35,049 --> 01:34:38,610
A bad divorce left you
with virtually nothing financially.

1365
01:34:38,686 --> 01:34:42,247
You had about $9,000 to your name,
correct?

1366
01:34:43,725 --> 01:34:45,283
Months before your divorce...

1367
01:34:45,560 --> 01:34:49,462
...you and your wife purchased tickets
to Hong Kong.

1368
01:34:50,231 --> 01:34:52,290
You were going to go together...

1369
01:34:52,800 --> 01:34:56,930
...but after the separation,
she cashed hers in.

1370
01:34:58,072 --> 01:34:59,539
What did you do with yours?

1371
01:35:00,808 --> 01:35:01,775
I used it.

1372
01:35:02,977 --> 01:35:04,808
He used it.

1373
01:35:06,314 --> 01:35:08,646
With only $9,000 to his name...

1374
01:35:08,916 --> 01:35:12,147
...with his life in a rut,
he didn't do the safe thing.

1375
01:35:12,820 --> 01:35:14,788
He could have cashed in his ticket.

1376
01:35:14,856 --> 01:35:18,792
But he said,
"To hell with it, I'm going to Hong Kong."

1377
01:35:20,628 --> 01:35:23,563
That alone, in my book, takes a lot of guts.

1378
01:35:24,098 --> 01:35:26,498
But, Your Honors, it just begins there.

1379
01:35:26,734 --> 01:35:29,430
Let us go to 36-9-16.

1380
01:35:30,438 --> 01:35:33,168
Los Angeles lnternational Airport.

1381
01:35:33,841 --> 01:35:35,672
You're in seat 41 B.

1382
01:35:39,580 --> 01:35:41,104
Between A and C.

1383
01:35:41,449 --> 01:35:42,882
Yes, it is.

1384
01:35:43,885 --> 01:35:46,615
I'm sitting between people
all the way to Asia?

1385
01:35:47,055 --> 01:35:48,283
Yes, you are.

1386
01:35:50,191 --> 01:35:52,352
Is coach completely full?

1387
01:35:52,627 --> 01:35:53,958
Oh, yes.

1388
01:35:58,166 --> 01:36:00,225
Any space left in first class?

1389
01:36:03,037 --> 01:36:04,334
There's one seat left.

1390
01:36:05,473 --> 01:36:08,374
-What's the price difference?
-Round-trip?

1391
01:36:10,378 --> 01:36:14,041
It's an additional $3,194.

1392
01:36:20,054 --> 01:36:21,385
I'll take it.

1393
01:36:24,992 --> 01:36:27,153
This man just spent one-third...

1394
01:36:27,261 --> 01:36:31,095
...of his entire life savings
to be more comfortable.

1395
01:36:32,166 --> 01:36:33,497
What does that say?

1396
01:36:33,768 --> 01:36:37,363
As stressed out and crazy
as his life was at that moment...

1397
01:36:37,672 --> 01:36:40,436
...the little boy inside him cried out:

1398
01:36:40,675 --> 01:36:45,442
"I need this. Don't worry about money.
We'll get it back. Be nice to me."

1399
01:36:46,514 --> 01:36:48,311
And he was.

1400
01:36:51,018 --> 01:36:54,181
I feel Mr. Miller is sufficiently past
the fears...

1401
01:36:54,422 --> 01:36:59,359
...that would keep him from being
a remarkable citizen of the Universe.

1402
01:37:00,027 --> 01:37:04,361
I wholeheartedly recommend
full onward movement.

1403
01:37:05,266 --> 01:37:06,426
I rest.

1404
01:37:07,135 --> 01:37:08,568
Miss Foster, you're up.

1405
01:37:13,374 --> 01:37:17,640
At this point, I would like to show
my final summation scene.

1406
01:37:18,446 --> 01:37:19,174
Proceed.

1407
01:37:20,047 --> 01:37:23,210
My scene takes place not there, but here.

1408
01:37:24,785 --> 01:37:26,776
We're showing something from here?

1409
01:37:27,121 --> 01:37:28,281
Yes, we are.

1410
01:37:28,422 --> 01:37:30,481
I was told we're not doing that anymore.

1411
01:37:30,558 --> 01:37:32,389
No one told you that.

1412
01:37:33,127 --> 01:37:34,355
What are we seeing?

1413
01:37:34,795 --> 01:37:36,194
Something from last night.

1414
01:37:37,899 --> 01:37:41,300
Please watch this
and tell me what you were feeling.

1415
01:37:48,976 --> 01:37:50,739
Want to spend the night with me?

1416
01:37:50,978 --> 01:37:53,071
More than anything in the world.

1417
01:37:54,682 --> 01:37:55,876
I don't think I can.

1418
01:37:56,417 --> 01:37:58,044
I don't think I should.

1419
01:37:58,119 --> 01:37:59,108
Why?

1420
01:38:00,188 --> 01:38:03,248
If I had a fire scene like you,
I'd feel differently.

1421
01:38:03,491 --> 01:38:05,686
I'd stay here. I'd never leave.

1422
01:38:05,993 --> 01:38:09,326
But I've been defending myself so hard...

1423
01:38:09,497 --> 01:38:11,897
...and I don't want to be judged anymore.

1424
01:38:12,433 --> 01:38:15,630
I have this wonderful feeling inside of me,
but I'm....

1425
