about the world Mr. Miller came from.

1436
01:39:11,659 --> 01:39:14,127
It's filled with problems
you no longer have:

1437
01:39:14,729 --> 01:39:19,223
Deadly diseases,
confusing identities, changing attitudes.

1438
01:39:19,600 --> 01:39:23,036
Perhaps he was worried
about getting a disease.

1439
01:39:23,904 --> 01:39:26,065
Were you worried about getting a disease?

1440
01:39:26,574 --> 01:39:28,838
I didn't think she had a disease. No.

1441
01:39:29,076 --> 01:39:30,839
But you didn't know.

1442
01:39:30,911 --> 01:39:32,435
We're getting off the point.

1443
01:39:32,513 --> 01:39:36,347
We've never been near the point!
You're getting him both ways!

1444
01:39:36,417 --> 01:39:40,251
When he's brave and then does something
you don't like, you show the follow-up.

1445
01:39:40,588 --> 01:39:42,920
Or you blame him for not having any.

1446
01:39:43,090 --> 01:39:47,254
This is an example of something
he wanted to do. And he didn't...

1447
01:39:47,695 --> 01:39:49,526
...because he was afraid.

1448
01:39:49,864 --> 01:39:51,331
